FTC to probe FB AMZNDOJ to probe GOOGL AAPL FYI this is a probe they need to first investigate if antitrust laws were broken then a case needs to go to trial a judgement needs to be issued then appealed then potentially relitigated Expectation based on Microsoft case that a behaviour remedy will be issued not a breakup order to avoid a lengthy litigation appeals process FTC inquiry into Microsoft began in 1992 suit began on May 18 1998 On June 7 2000 the court ordered a breakup of Microsoft as its remedy DC Circuit Court of Appeals overturned Judge Jacksons rulings against Microsoft DOJ announced on September 6 2001 that it was no longer seeking to break up Microsoft and would instead seek a lesser antitrust penalty On November 2 2001 the DOJ reached an agreement with Microsoft to settle the case Milton Friedman Antitrust very quickly becomes regulation
